MY POSTED LOADS

                            POST LOAD

                            MY POTENTIAL LOADS
MY ACCOUNT
                        


























                FOR SHIPPERS AND FREIGHT BROKERS

1. Create your account.
                Registration is easy and takes only a few moments.

2. Post your loads.
                Once you’ve created your account, you can begin posting your freight immediately.
                Post a single load or create a template for loads you ship regularly.

3. We notify pre-screened carriers.
                Post.Bid.Ship. verifies its member carriers’ authority, insurance and safety record.
                When you post a load, you may invite your existing carriers to bid, plus invite
                Post.Bid.Ship.'s member carriers to bid.

4. Carriers submit competitive bids.
                We protect your contact information during the bidding process.

5. Review your bids.
                Post.Bid.Ship. notifies you by e-mail of all bids. You determine
                the time period during which you will accept bids, and can select a winner at any
                time.

6. Select a winning carrier.
                Once you select a winner, Post.Bid.Ship. reveals your contact information to the winning carrier, and helps you
                complete the transaction. You arrange payment terms directly with the carrier.

                FOR CARRIERS

1. Create your account.
                Registration is easy and takes only a few moments.

2. Set Freight Preferences tailored to your company’s capabilities.
                Receive email alerts when shippers and freight brokers post loads that match your equipment,
                origin and destination needs.

3. Review loads for free.
                Search our database for posted loads and place bids online to generate new business
                for your company.

4. Bid on loads for free.
                Bid on an unlimited number of loads for free. We protect your contact information during the
                bidding process.

5. Connect with shippers and Freight Brokers.
                Once you win a load, Post.Bid.Ship.
                reveals the shipper’s or freight brokers' contact information and helps you complete the transaction. You
                arrange freight payment terms directly with the shipper/freight broker.











